column5: Hey Rahul, I've set up the GitHub repo for our ML project. Did you get the invite?
Got it, Sneha. I'll clone it tonight and push the initial data cleaning script.
Did you check the documentation for the API? It's a bit tricky.
Looking at it now. I'll have the integration done by Friday.
Rahul, the script you pushed is throwing errors. Can you take a look?
Sorry, I was in a rush. I'll fix the bugs after dinner.
Are we meeting in the library at 2 PM for the sprint review?
Can't make it. My sister is visiting. Let's do it over Zoom later?
You missed the Zoom call last night. I had to finish the module myself.
So sorry Sneha! My internet went down. I'll handle the front-end part tonight to make up.
Happy Valentine's! Hope you and Anjali are having a good day. Don't forget the midnight deadline though.
Rahul? The portal closes in an hour. Where is your part of the code?
I'm so sorry. I fell asleep. I'll talk to the Professor and explain it was my fault.
Dr. Sharma was asking why our project is lagging. I didn't know what to tell him.
Tell him I'm handling the heavy processing. I'll have the results by Monday.
I saw you at the mall today! I tried to call out but you were walking fast with someone.
Oh, must have been someone else. I was at my cousin's place all day.
The final presentation is next week. We need at least 5 hours of solid work together.
Saturday? I'm free most of the day.
Wait, Anjali just told me you're going to a concert on Saturday. So when are we working?
I'll work on it Sunday morning. I promise.
You haven't replied to my emails. This is getting ridiculous, Rahul.
I'm removing your name from this module if you don't send the data by 5 PM.
Sending now! Please don't do that. I've just been having a really hard time lately.
I heard about the formal warning from Dr. Sharma. Get your act together, Rahul.
